      <TestDisplay tests={tests} />
    </div>
  );
}

export default ParentComponent;
```

In this code, `useState` is used to create a state variable `tests` and a setter function `setTests`. The `tests` variable is passed as a prop to the `TestDisplay` component.

The `useEffect` hook is used to simulate data coming in one by one from the server. It sets up an interval that runs every second. Each time the interval runs, it creates a new parameter object, adds it to the first test's children array, and then updates the `tests` state variable with the new array. This will cause the `TestDisplay` component to re-render with the new data, effectively adding a new row to the table.

